zm_pripyat is the first CS:S map based on the abandoned city of Pripyat, Ukraine, which was completely evacuated after the Chernobyl NPP accident in 1986.
This map took around 2 months to make.
Using real footage and artwork, I modelled this map to resemble the most to the actual city.
The main purpose of the map is to give the player a constant feeling of loneliness and of being in a long-forgotten place.

While relatively small, it has some of the classic zm style spots.

It features:

- Precise mapping of the abandoned city of Pripyat, using RL footage

- Climbing/Barricade spots

- Up to 64 players

- Pretty optimized to fit low-end machines.

- Radiation dangers, watch your steps!

Have fun in the forgotten streets of Pripyat...

The map features full optimization (I have many years experience with half life (1 and 2) mapping. I know how to work visleafs, func_details and hint brushes very well, so there is no questioning the FPS during runtime.

The map has a sewer who's water level can be raised by throwing a lever, the raising of the water disrupts other parts of the map (not all the map).
Nowhere on the map is perfectly safe, albeit a few cozy places for 1 person, but still killable.

It's a good map that offers dynamic gameplay and a lot of defensive strategies.

This was quick map for a map contest. Tons of custom models and textures.  I based the design on the mod type, lots of ways to block passages and change the game play. The trees look a little funky, but I needed some fuller than the standard models or other trees I created before. Since I am at the deadline, there is one problem there is custom pallet that is missing it's gib pieces due to a bspzip malfunction and did not have enough time to make an overview. Bots play very well, custom tuned nav mesh w/ nameplaces. There is a buy zone for the t's so the map plays as expect on regular CS:S. Comments are welcome.

After 5 years wasting my life with WoW, I'm back for Mapping and ZombieMod. My latest map was zm_Fidlers-Green and this is something like my warmup-map. 

The map is taking place in a little castle with 4 courtyards, which are connected with each other through the towers(Screenshot 5). The mapstyle is very simple and a mix of de_piranesi and zm_cbble. Even with the big filesize the map is relative small and easy to overview. The 64 spawnpoints are splitted across the whole map to avoid lagging start and blocking. Every yard has 5+ camping places, most of them are crates. The yard with the rocks and lake could be lagging with many players, the rest should be okay even with 64.

I would be happy to find a 40+ player Zombie Mod Server to test this baby in action, so please add Euerfeldi in Steam and tell me, when you add it to your mapcycle :)
Also if you find bugs/exploits, report them to me and I can delete them in the final version.

this is a zm map based on the game penumbra which is set in an abandoned mining shaft way below ground. this map has: 72 spawnpoints 3 secrets optimised for better fps a surprise around the 2 minute mark ;) the surprise is that when the round have been going for 3 minutes the light turns out! :O dont worry though it wont be completely dark. there is some emergency lights so you still can find your way around. and theres also your flashlight ;) anyways feel free to download comment and assess :D Changes in extended added an extra section with more camp and cade spots. this section being based around the kennels in penumbra black plague. added an extra secret added 1 more camp spot modified a few spots
